                     Software Management Policy and Plan

     Governor's Executive Order D-10-99
   Provides notification to departments and agencies of statewide policies
       for the acquisition and use of computer software to attain full
       compliance with provisions of federal and state copyright law.
     __________________________________________________________________

   Spacer Image
   HTML Format
   HTML Format Adobe Acrobat PDF Format
   Adobe Acrobat Reader Format Microsoft Word
   Microsoft Word
   Spacer Image
     __________________________________________________________________

     Management Memo #01-10 Adobe Acrobat Reader Format Microsoft Word
   Provides direction for state entities to attain full compliance with
       relevant provisions of federal and state copyright law relating to
       computer software.

   Spacer Image

     Software Management Policy (SIMM Vol ) Adobe Acrobat Reader Format
   Microsoft Word
   Incorporates the California Software Management Policy into the
       Statewide Information Management Manual (SIMM).

   Spacer Image

     Software Management Guidelines (SIMM Vol ) Adobe Acrobat Reader
   Format Microsoft Word
   Provides instructions for planning for and developing the Software
       Management Plan.

     * Supported Software List Form

     * Software Log

     * Software Inventory Worksheet

   Spacer Image

     Software Management Handbook Adobe Acrobat Reader Format Microsoft
   Word
   Provides additional documentation that state entities may find useful
       when developing their software management plans. DOIT will be using
       this internal handbook in the review of the Software Management
       Plans.

   Spacer Image

   CIO Work Group Computing Steering Committee

   DOIT will soon be creating a self-governing CIO Steering Committee to
   provide guidance to DOIT on a variety of topics and issues that impact
   Work Group Computing and computer desktop management including Software
   Management. If you are interested in serving on this committee, please
   contact Rhane Vennes at (916) 445-5899 or via e-mail
   rvennes@doit.ca.gov.
